# Docker build context excludes for scripts/workers/microvm/Dockerfile.browser-driver.
#
# This directory IS the build context (the Dockerfile is built with
# `docker build -f .../Dockerfile.browser-driver workers/browser-driver`), and
# Docker honours .dockerignore — NOT .gitignore. Several large git-ignored
# artifacts live here on a developer machine, most notably a ~715 MB `.venv/`
# created by scripts/workers/browser-driver/install.sh or by running the Python
# tests locally. Without these excludes that venv is uploaded to the daemon and
# baked into the `COPY . /src/browser-driver` layer; the later `rm -rf /src`
# hides it from the final filesystem but the layer still carries the bytes.
#
# Keep `src/` and `pyproject.toml` — they are what actually gets pip-installed.
.venv/
.pytest_cache/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.DS_Store

# Local resolver output, git-ignored (.gitignore:43). The Dockerfile pins
# versions explicitly rather than consuming this file.
uv.lock

# Tests are not installed into the rootfs; the worker package is installed
# non-editable and only `src/` matters at runtime.
tests/
